Document: AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachineplayback.rst
Summary: Provides playback control for an AnimationNodeStateMachine.

Inherits: AnimationNodeSync < AnimationNode < Resource < Object

This class provides playback control for an AnimationNodeStateMachine. It allows you to query the current state, transition between states, and manage the playback of animations within the state machine. You can access an instance of this class via the AnimationTree's get_animation_player().playback property.

Key Rule: This class is intended to be used with an AnimationTree and its associated AnimationNodeStateMachine. You cannot directly instantiate it.

Methods:

Method: get_current_node() → StringName
Returns the name of the current node in the state machine.

Method: get_travel_path() → PackedVector2Array
Returns the current travel path. This is used for blending between states.

Method: is_playing() → bool
Returns true if the state machine is currently playing.

Method: next_frame()
Advances the state machine by one frame. This is useful for manual control of the animation playback.

Method: seek(to_pos: float, update_nodes: bool = true)
Seeks to a specific position within the current animation.

Method: start()
Starts the state machine playback.

Method: stop()
Stops the state machine playback.

Method: travel(to_node: StringName)
Initiates a transition to the specified node. The transition will occur over time based on the connections in the state machine.

Method: is_in_transition() → bool
Returns true if the state machine is currently transitioning between states.

Method: get_travel_remaining() → float
Returns the remaining time for the current transition.

Method: get_current_node_progress() → float
Returns the progress of the current animation within the current state, as a value between 0.0 and 1.0.

Method: get_current_node_duration() → float
Returns the duration of the current animation within the current state.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachineplayback.rst
Summary: Provides playback control for an AnimationNodeStateMachine.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

This class provides playback control for an AnimationNodeStateMachine. It allows you to query the current state, transition between states, and manage the playback of animations within the state machine.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachineplayback.rst
Summary: Provides methods to control the playback of an AnimationTree state machine.
AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback
Allows control of AnimationTree state machines created with AnimationNodeStateMachine. Retrieve with "$AnimationTree.get("parameters/playback")".

GDScript:
    var state_machine = $AnimationTree.get("parameters/playback")
    state_machine.travel("some_state")

C#:
    var stateMachine = GetNode<AnimationTree>("AnimationTree").Get("parameters/playback").As<AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback>();
    stateMachine.Travel("some_state");
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachineplayback.rst
Summary: Provides methods to control the playback of an AnimationNodeStateMachine.

Inherits: AnimationNodeSync < AnimationNode < Resource < Object

This class provides methods to control the playback of an AnimationNodeStateMachine. It is returned by the AnimationTree.get(anim_tree_path) method when the node at anim_tree_path is an AnimationNodeStateMachine.

Methods:
Method: get_current_node() → StringName
Returns the name of the current animation node in the state machine.

Method: get_travel_path() → PackedVector2Array
Returns the current travel path in the state machine.

Method: is_playing() → bool
Returns true if the state machine is currently playing an animation.

Method: next_is_available() → bool
Returns true if the next animation in the transition is available.

Method: set_current(name: StringName)
Sets the current node to the node with the given name.

Method: start()
Starts the state machine playback.

Method: stop()
Stops the state machine playback.

Method: travel(to_node: StringName, jump: bool = false)
Transitions to the node with the given name. If jump is true, the transition will be immediate.

Method: is_transitioning() → bool
Returns true if the state machine is currently transitioning between states.

Method: get_travel_remaining() → float
Returns the remaining time for the current transition.

Method: get_current_play_position() → float
Returns the current playback position of the current animation.

Method: get_current_play_speed() → float
Returns the current playback speed of the current animation.

Method: get_current_play_speed_scale() → float
Returns the current playback speed scale of the current animation.

Method: is_in_transition() → bool
Returns true if the state machine is in a transition.

Method: get_transition_progress() → float
Returns the progress of the current transition, from 0.0 to 1.0.

Method: get_transition_duration() → float
Returns the duration of the current transition.

Method: get_transition_from() → StringName
Returns the name of the node from which the transition started.

Method: get_transition_to() → StringName
Returns the name of the node to which the transition is going.

Method: is_connected(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if there is a connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_total_weight(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → float
Returns the total weight of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_travel_time(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → float
Returns the travel time of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_blend_mode(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → int
Returns the blend mode of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_xfade_mode(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → int
Returns the xfade mode of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_switch_mode(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → int
Returns the switch mode of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_advance_mode(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → int
Returns the advance mode of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_advance_condition(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → StringName
Returns the advance condition of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_continue_mode(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → int
Returns the continue mode of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_continue_condition(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → StringName
Returns the continue condition of the connection between from_node and to_node.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_blending(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if blending.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_playing_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if playing backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_and_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self and backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_and_not_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self and not backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_and_not_backward_and_not_playing_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self and not backward and not playing backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_and_not_backward_and_playing_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
Returns true if the connection ignores if transitioning to self and not backward and playing backward.

Method: get_connection_ignore_if_transitioning_to_self_and_backward_and_not_playing_backward(from_node: StringName, to_node: StringName) → bool
